The paper deals with polytopes and their properties, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The Nested Polytope Problem (NPP) is a combinatorial optimization problem, which can be categorized under both discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the algebraic and topological properties of the NPP, which can be classified under algebraic geometry (cs.GT) and scientific computing (cs.SC).
